,5,'Very nice','Very nice. Easy to use. Got it to use with Amazon prime. Great combo.',1,0,2710),(3304,5,'The reviews are right-this is the best Kindle ever','I have used Kindle e-readers since Amazon introduced them years ago. All are good products and each new model has been a worthwhile upgrade. The Oasis is no exception, even from the highly touted Voyage model. It is expensive but the lightweight design, improved backlighting and battery cover are worth the additional expense for someone who reads frequently. This is definitely a good investment!',1,5,2711),(3305,5,'Fantastic','I purchased this as a gift for my wife and she loves it. She has an older Kindle, and she can\'t believe how much better the Oasis is.',1,3,2712),(3306,5,'Recommended by salesman','Works great for my grandson - had the Geek squad get a security plan setup on it and him acquainted with it. Battery life not great, but with a bright 10 inch screen on a THIN tablet is not surprising.',1,0,2713),(3307,5,'A gift for booklovers','Kindles are an excellent device for all book lovers',1,0,2714),(3308,4,'Voyager replacement','I got oasis yesterday, very lighweight compared to voyager, screen size comparable, like having actual page turn button, touchscreen seems kinda slow, the on/off button on top is improvement from back of voyager. cover does seem kind of flimsy, but supposed to be leather so will see how it holds up. finding it easier to hold with cover on, then removed. cover doesn\'t have separate charge port, so all charging is done thru kindle.',1,16,570),(3309,5,'Great E-Reader','Bought for my wife to upgrade from the original Kindle that she has worn out. Big step up from the original and should be good for another 8-10 years.',1,0,2715),(3310,5,'Great upgrade from my previous tablet.','I really like the auto on off feature. Volume control could be more ergonomic.',1,0,2716),(3311,4,'Powerful tablet with a nice size screen.','This Fire 10 is so much better than my old Kindle Fire HD that 