r WiFi network and then won\'t connect to the Kindle store. I don\'t think it\'s an issue with my network since all our other devices don\'t have the connectivity issues we had with this.',0,0,2744),(3349,3,'Okay so far, nothing to mentioned bad or especiall','Have had it for a while noe. A littlebit unusual to press so hard to change page but now starting to get used to it.',1,0,2745),(3350,5,'Amazing e-Reader','I am extremely happy with my new Kindle Voyage. The text is so sharp and crisp, the images look much better than on the Kindle Paperwhite. The device is extremely light and comfortable to hold, The adaptive front light works great. I have an iPad with the Kindle app, but the reading experience is so much better on my Kindle Voyage that don\'t regret the purchase one bit.',1,6,2746),(3351,3,'Experimental browser not great','The Kindle is great for just reading books, and the battery power is pretty good.The experimental browser is not very user friendly.',1,0,2747),(3352,5,'Excelent','Even though it is a little pricy, I like my new Kindle Voyage. It looks smaller, but it is because it\'s only the screen - no buttons. It is lightweight. You can scroll and turn pages with touch screen press or with physical small buttons on the side. It is automatically adjusts to different light conditions.',1,2,2748),(3353,4,'Great for what it is.','The original electronic book. Bought it for my wife who reads paper book at two to three a week. She\'s hooked and loves the Kindle.',1,2,497),(3354,5,'We bought it for our son and he loves it.','This kindle has easier viewing and the light adjustment is great.',1,0,2749),(3355,5,'Best Kindle Ever','This is so far the best Kindle I have ever owned. I love the screen and the resolution on it. The device out performs all of the other e readers on the market.',1,2,2750),(3356,5,'Love it!','Great looking display. Text is sharp and easy to read. The lighting of screen is wonderful for reading in lower light environments. This is a little more compact than the paper white model. I really love the page press button areas. Makes it so you can turn pages without adjusting your hand (as long as you are holding the voyage with your thumb resting in the button area). Sounds like a minor thing, but to me it\'s a big convenience!',1,9,2751),(3357,5,'Love it','Do most of my reading on one of my Kindles. Reading in sun light to no light is great. Easier to take anywhere size wise compared to a paperback. Really great for traveling. Download several books so I have a variety to read from. Long charge life.',1,1,2752),(3358,4,'Nice size for readings books electronically.','Good value, enjoy using it! I recommend this highly!',1,0,2753),(3359,5,'First kindle','Exceeded my expectation. Easy to read, books load and store with ease ! Great for saving space for avid reader. I can travel with many books dont have to worry about space',1,0,2754),(3360,5,'Awesome product','The best kindle that I ever had!It is great if you love reading and really want to have the feel of handling a book.Great for indoor and outdoor reading',1,2,2755),(3361,5,'Love the size of it','I would recommend this product. It works great and ver compact.',1,0,1145),(3362,5,'Best Kindle yet','This is my third Kindle and the best one yet. Love the new controls, the backlit page, the compact size and the ease of use. I would recommend the Kindle Voyage to all readers!',1,0,2756),(3363,5,'Perfect digital reader','The voyage is light and has a battery life of Two weeks. In different light settings the Voyage automatically adjusts. My eyes do not get tired from bad lighting. Reading outside is no problem for the Voyage.',1,0,2757),(3364,5,'Best E-Reader Available','I have been using the paperwhite for about 2 years now and this unit definitely beats it. The adaptive lighting is amazing and page turn buttons are quite useful. If you are looking for an E-Reader then this is the one for you.',1,1,2758),(3365,4,'Great alternative for reading','Great alternative to using tablet for reading. Only problem is trying to read a *.pdf file - it only enlarges the page and does not resize the document to easily move forward.',1,1,2759),(3366,5,'Good reading device','It is a good reading device. When the price drop to 100 dollar, it is a deal. You need to buy one at that level.',0,0,2760),(3367,5,'Great reader','I have both the Kindle Voyage and the low end Kindle Fire.While the $50.00 Fire is an amazing deal, for serious readin,g the Kindle Voyage is far easier on the eyes and has superior resolution. Now, it lacks many of the features of the less expensive Fire, such as color and online with Wifi; as a reader it is well organized and a pleasure.Truthfully, it isn\'t a whole lot better than the Paperwhite. It has a feature or two, but I\'m not sure it\'s worth the extra 60 dollars. It is still an excellent device.',1,0,129),(3368,5,'my wife love it','bought this e-reader as a gift for my wife and she loves it',1,0,2761),(3369,5,'Great Kindle','Nice size, nice look,love the feel of turning the page. Great reading experience.',1,0,2762),(3370,4,'Great Reader','I really enjoy reading on the new Kindle Voyage. Have had other Kindle models before this one. I especially like the brightness and lightness of it.Only drawback I needed to get use to was turning of pages being a little hesitant.',1,1,1672),(3371,5,'Love it','So much better than reading on an iPad, completely worth it. I guess my only complaint is the operating system still seems a little weak in terms of responsiveness and fluidity but doesn\'t really impact regular usage of just page turning, only felt while browsing the library/store etc.',1,0,2763),(3372,4,'Great product','I bought this game for my son, and he loves it..it is very entertaining.',1,0,1773),(3373,5,'Wife loves it','Works great, looks great, readable in bright sun...',1,0,2764),(3374,4,'Good For Leisure','Good for leisure/reading for fun. Not for students.',0,0,2765),(3375,4,'Kindle - better for reading than IPad','Really like the Kindle. The screen is very easy on the eyes, much better for reading than my Ipad!.',1,2,2766),(3376,5,'Love my Kindle Voyage.','Love my Kindle Voyage. The size is much smaller than my older Kindle and the weight is much less. This helps as I take fm Kindle everywhere. Love the touch screen features.',1,0,2767),(3377,5,'Love Reading with my new Kindle','One of the things I love the most about my new Kindle is it\'s size. It slides so nicely into my compact purse, protective case and all. Another thing I\'ve noticed is the lack of glare that I experienced with my old Kindle. It automatically adjusts to the light and I\'m looking forward to being able to read it on the beach without a struggle. I also love the battery life - it goes on forever. The case I bought makes it possible to stand my Kindle up in front of me and read while I\'m eating - a must for me - I never eat alone ;)',1,0,2768),(3378,5,'Best Kindle Best ereader yet','What a great ereader. Amazon continues its dominance in the ereader field with this entry. Light and comfortable to hold. Perfect combination of hepatic feedback buttons and adaptive back-lighting. Seems to stay charged forever even with regular use. I would definitely recommend this and would buy again.',1,0,2769),(3379,5,'The best e-reader on the market','excellent screen, the small changes to the form make a huge different (I adore the flatness so much), and the brightness is a perfect for daylight. IMO, worth the cost',1,0,2770),(3380,5,'best e-reader !','Kindle Voyage is easily the best e-reader with an impressive high-resolution display and it is very thin and light weight too. Loving it.',1,0,2771),(3381,5,'I love the Kindle Voyage','This is my first kindle but I\'m loving it. I picked it up a few days after it was released. One of the things I love the most is I\'m a reader but I am not a car owner so I get almost everywhere by bike. I got tired of lugging around heavy hardcover books from the library;